cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.MA 

The paper deals with the unit-demand pricing problem, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT) and involves dynamic programming (cs.DS) and probabilistic techniques (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the statistical properties of revenue distributions (cs.LG) and establishes structural properties of approximately-optimal and near-optimal solutions (cs.MA).
